<p>The <code>nbsp</code> function converts spaces to non-breaking spaces (<code>&amp;nbsp;</code>).</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'Hello World' | nbsp{close}</pre>
<p>Result: <b>{echo 'Hello World' | nbsp}</b></p>

<h2>Prevent Wrapping</h2>
<pre>{open}echo '10 USD' | nbsp{close}</pre>
<p>Price: {echo '10 USD' | nbsp}</p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo 'New York City' | nbsp | bold{close}</pre>
<p>City: {echo 'New York City' | nbsp | bold}</p>

<pre>{open}echo '100 km' | trim | nbsp{close}</pre>
<p>Distance: {echo '100 km' | trim | nbsp}</p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Use to prevent line breaks between words that should stay together.</p>
